The course provides a survey of the history of sport psychology and research methods, the  role of cognitive processes in connection with physical activity,  personality theories, emotions and motivation in the context of both sport and exercise psychology. Also, social processes and main intervention  methods of sport psychology are included.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide knowledge about the seminal studies, contemporary themes, and application of sport and exercise psychology in athletic training and exercise and skills to support mental health in sport and exercise optimally.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of this course, the student will be expected to: 1. have deep knowledge in a seminal study of sport or exercise psychology and describe contemporary knowledge derived from this particular research; 2. has planned, conducted, and evaluated a psychological intervention inspired by the seminal study that they have selected for deeper study; 3. analyze the aims and principles of applying pedagogical psychology in athletic training and exercise.
